results.description:
White Rock lake, Winfrey Point
Photo 1:  A 2nd Species Of Feather-legged Fly
A few flowers down from where I found the all black feather-legged fly, I found this one.  I figured the color difference was simply a gender difference.  I was wrong.  It turned out to be a totally different species but same genus.  So cool, I got 2 new species within a couple of minutes.  
Photo 2:  Orange Abdomen & Black Feathers
Turns out it was good to keep this shot because it identified the gender, the females are black on the end of the abdomen & this shows a male with orange all the way down.  So nice to get a twofer.
